Serialized Form

  • Package app

    • Class app.Album extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • albumName

          java.lang.String albumName
          Name of the album.

        • beginDate

          java.time.LocalDateTime beginDate
          Date-Time of the earliest photo in our album.

        • endDate

          java.time.LocalDateTime endDate
          Date-Time of the most recent photo in our album.

        • numOfPhotos

          int numOfPhotos
          Number of photos in our album

        • photos

          java.util.List<Photo> photos
          List of all the photos held in our album.

    • Class app.Photo extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • caption

          java.lang.String caption
          User made caption for the photo.

        • location

          java.lang.String location
          Stores the address of the photo on the user's machine. Intention is to then refer to the photo and display it via URL.

        • photoDate

          java.time.LocalDateTime photoDate
          Date for the "last modified" attribute of the photo file on the user's system in ISO-8601. Has date and time which considers the user's timezone.

        • photoTags

          java.util.List<Tag> photoTags
          Each photo has a list of tags that the user can refer to in order to find this photo.

    • Class app.Tag extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • multipleValues

          boolean multipleValues
          Boolean that represents if the tag can take on multiple values or not. I.e person could take multiple values, but the photo is only taken in ONE location.

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          Represents the name of the tag. I.e person, location, etc.

        • values

          java.util.List<java.lang.String> values
          Represents the values associated with the tag. I.e for the tag person, we could have Patricia, mary, etc.

    • Class app.User extends java.lang.Object implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • albums

          java.util.List<Album> albums
          List of Albums which are associated with the user.

        • availableTags

          java.util.List<Tag> availableTags
          List of tags that are visible to the user for adding to photos.

        • userName

          java.lang.String userName
          String which represents the name of the user.
